<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56959a77-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s507"><num value="507">§ 507.</num><heading> Appointment of judges</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may appoint civilian employees of the department in which the Coast Guard is operating as appellate military judges, available for assignment to the Coast Guard Court of Criminal Appeals as provided for in <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s866/a">section 866(a) of title 10</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56959a78-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/111/281/tII/s201/a">Pub. L. 111–281, title II, § 201(a)</ref>, <date date="2010-10-15">Oct. 15, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/2909">124 Stat. 2909</ref>, § 153; renumbered § 507, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s105/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 105(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4200">132 Stat. 4200</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id56959a79-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">
